<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-05T13:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-05T13:04:00-05:00" n="960" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d960">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3057.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi> (<hi rend="italic">via El Paso,
                                        Tex.</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-05T11:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The warning to leave isolated points issued to Americans by Ambassador
                            can not be communicated to the hundreds of Americans in remote mining
                            sections without special messengers. I request definite instructions.
                            Railway communications closed nearly everywhere. Dictatorship exists
                            here now. Communications closed south in order to prevent apprehended
                            advance Federals against Chihuahua.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marion Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>